(1)
194 Bainbridge Street, south side, near Reid Ave. A view of the Moses Suydam House. In front crossing Bainbridge Street, was the Jamaica Turnpike Road in 1869, and in front of the house, stood the toll house to Brooklyn.

March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, another angle.

May 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
